  "combined_text": "--- Main Page ---\nAtlanta's Margarita Bar & Taqueria | Guac y Margys | GyM\nLooking for a Beltline Restaurant to host your next event? Book Guac y Margys and we promise to make it an unforgettable one!\nGroup Event Request\nSTAY HYDRATED\nGET GUAC HARD ABS\nDON'T MISS A DAY\nCOME SQUAT A WHILE\nPrevious\nNext\nTHE FOODS\nChips, salsa, queso and our famous guacamole are served all day, every day, at all three locations. Our Midtown location serves a full menu including tacos, burritos, salads and more!\nMORE\nTHE DRANKS\nAll our margaritas are made fresh - #nomix. GyM is also equipped with a full bar, so even if margaritas aren't your thing, we've still got you covered.\nMORE\nCOMMUNITY\nAll three of our owners were either born in Atlanta or have lived here for over 10 years. We love our city and are dedicated to giving back.\nMORE\nGYM |\nTHE FOODS\nIf we HAD to put ourselves in a box, taqueria is the closest label, but who likes labels?! We prefer to say that the taco is really just a vessel for our creativity. We always have a meat option for the carnivores and a veggie option for the vegetarians, but what makes up the taco is probably different from what you're used to. For example, our cauliflower taco is one of our most popular tacos! And don't get us started on the Tequila Chicken Taco, ATLien style 🌮 (seriously, it's the bomb). Come try âem all! 😄\nGYM |\nTHE DRANKS\nAll our margaritas are made fresh - #nomix. We're known for our infused tequilas, so be sure to try our 'Forever, Forever Ever' or 'Strawberry Pineapple Holla!' for a different take on this classic drink 🍹\nGYM |\nCOMMUNITY\nAll three of our owners were either born in Atlanta or have lived here for over 10 years 🌃  We love our city and are dedicated to giving back. Since we opened our doors, we have donated over $15,000 to local nonprofits. 💚\nGYM |\nOUR STORY\nEver been on a run along the Atlanta BeltLine, seen an awesome space for lease, and thought, \"Man, I'd love to open a bar right there...\" Well, that's how GUAC Y MARGYS began 🏃 There's a bit more to the story, but to keep it short and simple - we're here to be Atlanta's Margarita Bar! We make carefully crafted margaritas that are all about taste, not sugar; and guacamole that will revolutionize your taste buds. 👅\n\n--- Page: /menu-gym1.pdf ---\n%PDF-1.6\r%����\n10 0 obj\n<\n>\nendobj\nxref\n10 24\n0000000016 00000 n\n0000001002 00000 n\n0000001063 00000 n\n0000001311 00000 n\n0000001474 00000 n\n0000001516 00000 n\n0000094766 00000 n\n0000185858 00000 n\n0000256361 00000 n\n0000256423 00000 n\n0000256467 00000 n\n0000256512 00000 n\n0000326684 00000 n\n0000396873 00000 n\n0000467042 00000 n\n0000467090 00000 n\n0000552752 00000 n\n0001377994 00000 n\n0001450850 00000 n\n0001454330 00000 n\n0001454365 00000 n\n0001454929 00000 n\n0001455013 00000 n\n0000000776 00000 n\ntrailer\n<\n<11C7835620B8B2110A00291F8E23CD7C>]/Prev 1983116>>\nstartxref\n0\n%%EOF\n33 0 obj\n<\n>stream\nh�b```e``v\u0005���\u0019D\u0018\u0010@��\u0005(�����𸰀�a&DxU�ᅞ\u0006f��\u0006&��\u000e�\u0014\u0010�1�\u0019m\u0002Ң@,\u0006\u0016Q\u0006��\u001b����P�#/f-(��������a��OA����\u0018\u0018.�U�,/�)e�\u001e\u0000Ԡ(�`�`%� \u0001���A�a\u0003�f\u0004�_\u0000\u0001\u0006\u0000�6\u001cj\nendstream\nendobj\n11 0 obj\n<\n>\nendobj\n12 0 obj\n<\n>\nendobj\n13 0 obj\n<\n>/ExtGState<\n>/ProcSet[/PDF/ImageB/ImageC/ImageI]/XObject<\n>>>\nendobj\n14 0 obj\n<\n>\nendobj\n15 0 obj\n<\n>stream\nH�dW[nd�\r�?��\u0015���(R+�w��\u0000#\u000f 3\u0001n���T\u0015�vۍ\u0001�>e�\")�X����\u001f�v���\u001f��?��h����m���gk���_���=���ϸs4{���6��7�u��v�f�l��6��``\u000b\u0018m\u0013hwx\u0000�{�( �?>\u0004����\u0018\u0017��YVFO�\u0018s\u0017\u0010=�\t��˟��\u001c>�\u0018^�璃\u0001oRA�5kŶ-;q�5\nJ�$�-\u000b�#�\"��i�{Y'\u0014���d�yÝ'4�\u000f�9�\u0017D�*\u0019qG~~ÿ�˛�\u0015y���6��}�9ӿ�o�\u0000\u001a\u00173��\u0018��{�|���\u0001Ê�W��y\u0019魲� ߢ���F�\u0001\u0019oAU1��1\n�>\u0004��\u0005l�K+\u0016\u0013jq\u000f����\u0007P7,�'{������p��\u0016�\u001bg\n�